review text: No monster descriptions, just stats. If there is some way remove the ads then they've hidden it somewhere.
developer reply text: Unlocking either the dm tools or the character manager also removes the ads.

review text: Wizard

Would be very useful if it wasn't so buggy. Current HP sometimes don't save or are not carried over from battle mode, no direct support for Druid Wild Shape, prepared spells and skill ranks get reset whenever they scroll out of view, no quick way to tell how many spellslots are used or still useable...
Useful
I'm not a D&D player but this app quite good reference for writing fantasy as a reference. Feature request: Create content in offline mode with built-in template and example.
developer reply text: Thank you for the nice review. We will take your feature request into consideration.

review text: This should be called the INcomplete reference doing a search for a class brings up only one way to play that class. Wizard for example only shows one school to choose from where there should be eight. With absolutely no reference to any other material from any other search criteria. At best this app is a good reference point for a wide range of topics, but if you want to actually know about any single topic you can find more in the basic phb
developer reply text: Thank you for the review. The app comes initially with the SRD 5 content (an open source subset of the phb). For a lot of additional content, have a look at our forums on complete-reference.com/forum from there you can easily add content to the app.

developer reply text: Thank you for the review. We will add new content again soon, we had some different focusses to work on the last period.

review text: Awkwardly missing wood elves, drow, cleric domains ect.... So you're saying a "complete reference" can miss come content I need to rummage on some internet forms to collect?.... Don't get me wrong, being able to import and add information is a great feature and full credit to you. But you're not complete are you?
developer reply text: Be sure to checkout our forums at complete-reference.com/forum . You can get a lot of content from there. You can import the content with one click in the app. The app does initially come with the complete SRD 5, which is a subset of the content published open source. So indeed, considering all the content it is not complete from the start.

review text: This app is amazing! There is a lot of content on here that you would need to pay alot otherwise to get. That being said, I have a few issues with the character creator. The character creator doesn't allow you to equip your armor and weapons. All equipment has to be plugged in manually. And it doesn't show you how many spell slots you have per long rest. That being said, I love this app! But I feel the character creator could do with a few tweaks, personally. Keep up the great work guys!
Great app for character building!
